history.content:
Hi,

I know instructors make no decisions on the waitlist but wondering if someone here can help me. There are 26 people on the waitlist and 315 enrolled. Do the people making the decisions over the waitlist think that all these students could get in? I am asking because there are several sections with seats available for discussions and it would be nice if I can get reasonable info about getting in. I need one upper division CS course and I would love to take this class. There is a fee that I have put into the course and I don't want to get dropped :(
